This paper discusses energy consumption in database management systems, which is a topic closely related to the field of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also presents techniques for managing energy consumption during query processing, which involves aspects of computer architecture (cs.AR) and systems engineering (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses research issues in the emerging area of energy-efficient data processing, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) or performance analysis (cs.PF).
